    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/321: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reber</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 22, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Department’s 80 [<hi rend="italic">90</hi>], October 18, 6 p.m.<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d325fn40">Not printed.</note> A copy of the Commission’s report was
                    delivered by Dr. Johnson to the Department on October 21. This copy is being
                    studied. You may, in your discretion, so inform President King.</p>
                <pb facs="0458" n="364" xml:id="pg_364"/>
                <p>If the press raises the question, the Department will reply substantially as in
                    the two sentences above. The Department will keep you informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
